# Keep documentation in sync with code

When you change **user-visible behavior**, **LSP capabilities**, **formatter rules**, **CLI contracts**, **pixi tasks**, or **project layout**, update documentation in the **same change** (do not defer).

## mdBook

Documentation is rendered with [mdBook](https://rust-lang.github.io/mdBook/). The book source lives in `docs/`.

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| [docs/SUMMARY.md](../docs/SUMMARY.md) | **Table of contents** — defines sidebar navigation and chapter order for the generated site |
| [docs/README.md](../docs/README.md) | Book landing page (linked first in `SUMMARY.md`) |

**`SUMMARY.md` is special:** fixed filename, not numbered. Every page that should appear in the built book must be linked from `SUMMARY.md`. When you add, remove, or rename a chapter, update `SUMMARY.md` in the same change.

Use nested `# Section` headings in `SUMMARY.md` for sidebar groups. Link targets use paths relative to `docs/`:

```markdown
# Summary

[Introduction](README.md)

# User guide

- [Getting Started](2_getting-started.md)
- [Architecture](4_architecture.md)

# Development

- [Build](development/1_build.md)
```

Do not link pages in `SUMMARY.md` until the target file exists (mdBook fails on missing chapters).

## Naming convention

Chapter files use a numeric prefix so they sort in reading order:

```
{N}_{slug}.md
```

- `N` is a positive integer (`1`, `2`, `3`, …) with no zero-padding.
- `slug` is lowercase with hyphens (e.g. `getting-started`, `lsp-features`).
- **Each directory has its own sequence.** Restart numbering at `1_` in every subdirectory.

**Exceptions (do not number):** `SUMMARY.md`, `README.md` (book intro in `docs/`).

Examples:

```
docs/SUMMARY.md
docs/README.md
docs/2_getting-started.md
docs/development/1_build.md
docs/internal/1_design.md
```

When adding a chapter, pick the next number in that directory, create the file, then add a bullet to `SUMMARY.md`. Renumber only when restructuring (update `SUMMARY.md` and cross-links in the same change).

## Doc tree

| File | Update when you change… |
|------|-------------------------|
| [docs/SUMMARY.md](../docs/SUMMARY.md) | Any chapter added, removed, renamed, or regrouped |
| [docs/README.md](../docs/README.md) | Book intro, “Last verified against”, high-level project overview |
| [docs/2_getting-started.md](../docs/2_getting-started.md) | Setup, pixi workflow, binaries, editor integration |
| [docs/3_principles.md](../docs/3_principles.md) | Goals, non-goals, UX values |
| [docs/4_architecture.md](../docs/4_architecture.md) | Crates, module map, parser/LSP/formatter pipeline |
| [docs/5_lsp-features.md](../docs/5_lsp-features.md) | LSP methods, diagnostics, completion, navigation |
| [docs/6_formatter.md](../docs/6_formatter.md) | Formatting rules, alignment, dialect-specific behavior |
| [docs/7_limitations.md](../docs/7_limitations.md) | Known constraints, unsupported dialect constructs |
| [docs/development/1_build.md](../docs/development/1_build.md) | Pixi tasks, CI, release builds |
| [docs/internal/1_design.md](../docs/internal/1_design.md) | Internal design notes (may lead public docs; keep aligned) |
| [README.md](../README.md) | Quick start, task examples |

Files listed above that do not exist yet should be created when the corresponding code or behavior is first introduced—and linked from `SUMMARY.md` at the same time.

## When to update

Update docs if you touch any of:

- Rust source (`src/**`, `crates/**`, or workspace `Cargo.toml` files)
- Tree-sitter grammar or queries (`tree-sitter-spice/**`, `queries/**`)
- `pixi.toml` (especially `[tasks]`)
- LSP capability registration or handler behavior
- Formatter output or CLI flags
- VS Code / editor extension integration under this repo
- mdBook config (`book.toml`) or book structure

Skip doc updates only for pure refactors with **no** behavior, LSP, formatter, CLI, or task-name changes.

## Checklist before finishing

- [ ] Relevant doc(s) describe behavior **after** your change
- [ ] [README.md](../README.md) examples still run as written
- [ ] No stale references (removed tasks, wrong paths, old unnumbered filenames)
- [ ] New chapters follow `{N}_{slug}.md` and are linked from [docs/SUMMARY.md](../docs/SUMMARY.md)
- [ ] LSP/formatter tables match implemented capabilities (not aspirational design-only text)
- [ ] Bump “Last verified against” in [docs/README.md](../docs/README.md) when materially refreshing docs

## Style

- Factual, present tense; tables for LSP methods, formatter options, and CLI flags
- Prefer editing the numbered chapter doc over duplicating content in multiple files
- Keep `SUMMARY.md` lean—navigation only, not chapter content
